Thinly slice the aubergine lengthwise and toss with olive oil and sea salt, then cook on a hot barbecue or chargrill until charred and tender.Toss the remaining vegetables in olive oil and sea salt and cook on a hot chargrill or barbecue until charred and tender.Place all the cooked vegetables in a large bowl.For the dressing, combine the garlic, mustard, capers and vinegars in a bowl, season with sea salt to taste and stir in the olive oil. Add the parsley leaves and mix well to combine.Pour the dressing over the vegetables and toss well to coat them.